172  private void doGGKTestPreparedStatement(int[] values, boolean useUpdate)
173  throws Exception {
174  // Generate the the multiple replace command
175  StringBuffer cmd = new StringBuffer("REPLACE INTO testggk VALUES ");
176  int newKeys = 0;
177 
178  for (int i = 0; i < values.length; i++) {
179  cmd.append("(");
180 
181  if (values[i] == 0) {
182  cmd.append("NULL");
183  newKeys += 1;
184  } else {
185  cmd.append(values[i]);
186  }
187 
188  cmd.append(", ");
189  cmd.append(count++);
190  cmd.append("), ");
191  }
192 
193  cmd.setLength(cmd.length() - 2); // trim the final ", "
194 
195  // execute and print it
196  System.out.println(cmd.toString());
197 
198  PreparedStatement pStmt = this.conn.prepareStatement(cmd.toString(),
199  Statement.RETURN_GENERATED_KEYS);
200 
201  if (useUpdate) {
202  pStmt.executeUpdate();
203  } else {
204  pStmt.execute();
205  }
206 
207  // print out what actually happened
208  System.out.println("Expect " + newKeys
209  + " generated keys, starting from " + nextID);
210 
211  this.rs = pStmt.getGeneratedKeys();
212  StringBuffer res = new StringBuffer("Got keys");
213 
214  int[] generatedKeys = new int[newKeys];
215  int i = 0;
216 
217  while (this.rs.next()) {
218  if (i < generatedKeys.length) {
219  generatedKeys[i] = this.rs.getInt(1);
220  }
221 
222  i++;
223 
224  res.append(" " + this.rs.getInt(1));
225  }
226 
227  int numberOfGeneratedKeys = i;
228 
229  assertTrue(
230  "Didn't retrieve expected number of generated keys, expected "
231  + newKeys + ", found " + numberOfGeneratedKeys,
232  numberOfGeneratedKeys == newKeys);
233  assertTrue("Keys didn't start with correct sequence: ",
234  generatedKeys[0] == nextID);
235 
236  System.out.println(res.toString());
237 
238  // Read and print the new state of the table
239  this.rs = this.stmt.executeQuery("SELECT id, val FROM testggk");
240  System.out.println("New table contents ");
241 
242  while (this.rs.next())
243  System.out.println("Id " + this.rs.getString(1) + " val "
244  + this.rs.getString(2));
245 
246  // Tidy up
247  System.out.println("");
248  nextID += newKeys;
249  }

5947  .prepareStatement("INSERT INTO testBug41532(ID, S1, S2, S3, D1,"

5952  + " VALUES(N2)");

5969  Types.TIMESTAMP);

6920  public void testExecutionPlanForSlowQueries() throws Exception {
6921  // once slow query (with execution plan) warning is sent to System.err, we capture messages sent here to check
6922  // proper operation.
6923  final class TestHandler {
6924  // System.err diversion handling
6925  PrintStream systemErrBackup = null;
6926  ByteArrayOutputStream systemErrDetour = null;
6927 
6928  // Connection handling
6929  Connection testConn = null;
6930 
6931  TestHandler() {
6932  systemErrBackup = System.err;
6933  systemErrDetour = new ByteArrayOutputStream(8192);
6934  System.setErr(new PrintStream(systemErrDetour));
6935  }
6936 
6937  boolean containsSlowQueryMsg(String lookFor) {
6938  String errMsg = systemErrDetour.toString();
6939  boolean found = false;
6940 
6941  if (errMsg.indexOf("Slow query explain results for '" + lookFor + "'") != -1) {
6942  found = true;
6943  }
6944  systemErrDetour.reset();
6945  // print message in original OutputStream.
6946  systemErrBackup.print(errMsg);
6947  return found;
6948  }
6949 
6950  void undoSystemErrDiversion() throws IOException {
6951  systemErrBackup.print(systemErrDetour.toString());
6952  systemErrDetour.close();
6953  System.setErr(systemErrBackup);
6954  systemErrDetour = null;
6955  systemErrBackup = null;
6956  }
6957 
6958  @SuppressWarnings("synthetic-access")
6959  Connection getNewConnectionForSlowQueries() throws SQLException {
6960  releaseConnectionResources();
6961  testConn = getConnectionWithProps("logSlowQueries=true,explainSlowQueries=true");
6962  Statement st = testConn.createStatement();
6963  // execute several fast queries to unlock slow query analysis and lower query execution time mean
6964  for (int i = 0; i < 25; i++) {
6965  st.executeQuery("SELECT 1");
6966  }
6967  return testConn;
6968  }
6969 
6970  void releaseConnectionResources() throws SQLException {
6971  if (testConn != null) {
6972  testConn.close();
6973  testConn = null;
6974  }
6975  }
6976  }
6977 
6978  TestHandler testHandler = new TestHandler();
6979  Statement testStatement = null;
6980 
6981  try {
6982  if (versionMeetsMinimum(5, 6, 3)) {
6983  createTable("testWL4897", "(f1 INT NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY, f2 CHAR(50))");
6984 
6985  // when executed in the following sequence, each one of these queries take approximately 1 sec.
6986  final String[] slowQueries = {
6987  "INSERT INTO testWL4897 VALUES (SLEEP(0.5) + 1, 'MySQL'), (SLEEP(0.5) + 2, 'Connector/J')",
6988  "SELECT * FROM testWL4897 WHERE f1 + SLEEP(0.5) = f1",
6989  "REPLACE INTO testWL4897 VALUES (SLEEP(0.33) + 2, 'Database'), (SLEEP(0.33) + 3, 'Connector'), (SLEEP(0.33) + 4, 'Java')",
6990  "UPDATE testWL4897 SET f1 = f1 * 10 + SLEEP(0.25)",
6991  "DELETE FROM testWL4897 WHERE f1 + SLEEP(0.25) = f1" };
6992 
6993  for (String query : slowQueries) {
6994  testStatement = testHandler.getNewConnectionForSlowQueries().createStatement();
6995  testStatement.execute(query);
6996  assertTrue("A slow query explain results warning should have been issued for: '" + query + "'.",
6997  testHandler.containsSlowQueryMsg(query));
6998  testStatement.close();
6999  }
7000  } else {
7001  // only SELECT is qualified to log slow query explain results warning
7002  final String query = "SELECT SLEEP(1)";
7003 
7004  testStatement = testHandler.getNewConnectionForSlowQueries().createStatement();
7005  testStatement.execute(query);
7006  assertTrue("A slow query explain results warning should have been issued for: '" + query + "'.",
7007  testHandler.containsSlowQueryMsg(query));
7008  testStatement.close();
7009  }
7010 
7011  } finally {
7012  testHandler.releaseConnectionResources();
7013  testHandler.undoSystemErrDiversion();
7014  }
